1
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:44,320
How could I...

2
00:00:47,640 --> 00:00:48,920
Sheng Yuanzhou

3
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:51,600
You had people beat me up?

4
00:00:51,759 --> 00:00:52,600
You're awake.

5
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:54,759
My son!

6
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:56,320
You're finally awake!

7
00:00:56,719 --> 00:00:59,280
How could you slam your head on the road?

8
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:02,359
Luckily, Siqi and your friend brought you.

9
00:01:02,679 --> 00:01:03,679
I hope you're not badly hurt.

10
00:01:03,799 --> 00:01:05,079
Ma'am, don't worry.

11
00:01:05,079 --> 00:01:06,239
We'll take care of him.

12
00:01:07,239 --> 00:01:08,120
As long as you're okay.

13
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:10,359
Siqi, tonight...

14
00:01:10,439 --> 00:01:11,480
You should stay here.

15
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:13,959
For your family to go through this...

16
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:15,079
It's just awful.

17
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:17,000
I don't want to impose.

18
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,519
It's no imposition.

19
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:20,000
I brought you to

20
00:01:23,159 --> 00:01:24,040
Zhang Xiaobei's place

21
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:27,000
so you could hide here for now,

22
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,040
then leave after we deal with Jiang Min.

23
00:01:30,159 --> 00:01:32,280
Sheng Yuanzhou, this is my home.

24
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:34,560
You're quick to make decisions for me.

25
00:01:37,079 --> 00:01:37,760
How about

26
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:38,879
you two talk.

27
00:01:39,439 --> 00:01:40,319
Talk it out.

28
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:46,680
Sheng Yuanzhou, do you have a good plan?

29
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:50,480
Before,

30
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:53,319
you lost the shareholders' meeting.

31
00:01:53,439 --> 00:01:54,879
If we don't find a solution soon,

32
00:01:54,959 --> 00:01:56,319
Jiang Min really is going to

33
00:01:56,319 --> 00:01:57,319
take office as president.

34
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,840
Liu Li's watching you like a hawk.

35
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:02,400
Only if I get you out of her sight

36
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:04,000
will we have room to move.

37
00:02:04,239 --> 00:02:05,359
Then why come to my place?

38
00:02:06,519 --> 00:02:08,759
As they say, hiding in plain sight.

39
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,759
Your place is the safest spot right now.

40
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:12,319
Liu Li will definitely think

41
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:15,000
Siqi would go out to find help.

42
00:02:15,039 --> 00:02:17,159
If you don't leave Commoners' Alley,

43
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,599
you'll be safe for now.

44
00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:21,560
Those intimate photos were already leaked,

45
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:23,560
but it didn't do a thing.

46
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,800
Then we'll do it the proper way.

47
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,879
We'll lobby the shareholders.

48
00:02:26,919 --> 00:02:28,560
We tried that ages ago, okay?

49
00:02:28,639 --> 00:02:29,479
I know.

50
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,240
The logic is sound.

51
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,840
Jiang Min's Achilles' heel

52
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:35,680
is that he has no medical background.

53
00:02:35,719 --> 00:02:37,199
And doctors will never allow

54
00:02:37,199 --> 00:02:39,120
an outsider to come in and meddle.

55
00:02:40,879 --> 00:02:42,039
I've got all the materials ready.

56
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:42,919
So,

57
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,800
you want us to find a renowned doctor

58
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:48,719
and sway shareholders with medical skill.

59
00:02:49,199 --> 00:02:50,439
You've got plenty of manpower.

60
00:02:50,759 --> 00:02:51,879
Why make us do it?

61
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:54,319
I need to avoid suspicion.

62
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:55,879
My father supports

63
00:02:55,879 --> 00:02:57,240
Jiang Min's premium healthcare.

64
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,840
If I don't put on a show,

65
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,240
and have someone teach you a lesson,

66
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,840
do you think he'd let me off?

67
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:03,199
Right now, the top priority

68
00:03:03,199 --> 00:03:04,759
is to placate my father.

69
00:03:04,759 --> 00:03:06,439
Buy you some time.

70
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,280
Alright, it's getting late.

71
00:03:09,319 --> 00:03:10,240
Get to work.

72
00:03:12,479 --> 00:03:12,960
Oh, right.

73
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:14,360
Get up.

74
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:15,680
Your room is in the living room.

75
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:16,840
This is Siqi's room.

76
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,639
We're on a tight schedule.

77
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,080
This is my home.

78
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,319
Cut the nonsense and get to work.

79
00:03:21,319 --> 00:03:22,639
I know, I know it's your home.

80
00:03:22,919 --> 00:03:23,800
Stop with the useless stuff.

81
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:24,639
Turn left.

82
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,599
Xiaobei, Siqi, dinner's ready!

83
00:03:32,599 --> 00:03:33,280
Okay, thanks, ma'am.

84
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:33,800
Just set it there for now.

85
00:03:54,879 --> 00:03:55,759
I found him.

86
00:03:56,039 --> 00:03:57,199
I think he's a great fit.

87
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:58,599
Dr. Yiwen Zhang.

88
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,159
He's a top Chinese oncologist in Germany.

89
00:04:01,479 --> 00:04:03,039
Last month, he had an important paper

90
00:04:03,039 --> 00:04:04,120
published in The Lancet.

91
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,840
If he can come be the president,

92
00:04:05,919 --> 00:04:07,319
he'll definitely oust Jiang Min.

93
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:09,759
But he's lived in Germany for a long time,

94
00:04:10,039 --> 00:04:11,520
and his team is German too.

95
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:12,479
I don't speak German.

96
00:04:12,479 --> 00:04:14,120
Won't communication be a hassle?

97
00:04:14,159 --> 00:04:14,960
I do.

98
00:04:15,479 --> 00:04:16,199
Really?

99
00:04:16,879 --> 00:04:18,079
I like you.

100
00:04:18,279 --> 00:04:19,279
What does that mean?

101
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:27,519
When did you learn it?

102
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:28,800
I don't know either.

103
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:31,399
It feels like it was already in my head.

104
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,680
I know you're smart,

105
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,160
but you don't have to brag like that.

106
00:04:36,879 --> 00:04:38,279
But what did that line mean?

107
00:04:40,079 --> 00:04:41,800
The moon is beautiful tonight.

108
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:47,079
Don't tell me that's the only sentence you know.

109
00:04:47,959 --> 00:04:50,680
There's something about you

110
00:04:50,839 --> 00:04:52,680
that's impossible to forget.

111
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:54,920
Well?

112
00:04:55,319 --> 00:04:56,040
Believe me now?

113
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:57,920
I do.

114
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,639
Then I'll contact him.

115
00:05:08,399 --> 00:05:10,360
You're truly young and promising.

116
00:05:10,399 --> 00:05:11,360
Thank you.

117
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:12,720
This is Mr. Li.

118
00:05:12,959 --> 00:05:13,959
We've met before, Mr. Li. An honor.

119
00:05:14,079 --> 00:05:15,000
Likewise. A pleasure to meet you.

120
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,839
Let's keep in touch.

121
00:05:20,759 --> 00:05:21,800
Definitely, Mr. Li.

122
00:05:22,879 --> 00:05:24,000
Waiting for Dr. Yiwen Zhang?

123
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,839
You think if you hide,

124
00:05:26,199 --> 00:05:28,120
I won't find out what you're doing?

125
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:57,279
They're digging up profiles on so many doctors.

126
00:05:57,279 --> 00:05:58,279
What for?

127
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,519
Isn't it obvious?

128
00:06:01,439 --> 00:06:03,560
They want a famous doctor to prop it up

129
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:05,120
and push me out.

130
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:08,560
That damn Lin Siqi has quite a few tricks.

131
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,519
Next,

132
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:13,000
we figure out who she's going after

133
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,639
so we can prepare a response.

134
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,240
Got it.

135
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:21,199
What?

136
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,279
They want a German cancer specialist,

137
00:06:25,519 --> 00:06:26,240
Dr. Yiwen Zhang.

138
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:30,959
I know Dr. Yiwen Zhang's flight schedule.

139
00:06:35,959 --> 00:06:37,199
Dr. Zhang, let me handle it.

140
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,279
We're short on time.

141
00:06:39,439 --> 00:06:40,519
Let's go straight to the hospital.

142
00:06:41,439 --> 00:06:43,560
Give it up. He won't make it.

143
00:06:46,199 --> 00:06:46,600
Let's go.

144
00:06:53,959 --> 00:06:54,639
Sorry.

145
00:06:54,639 --> 00:06:57,319
The number you dialed is not answering.

146
00:06:59,319 --> 00:07:00,120
Everyone,

147
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,560
The inauguration for the president

148
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,680
of Benevolence Hospital begins now.

149
00:07:03,959 --> 00:07:04,920
Now let's welcome our...

150
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:05,519
Wait!

151
00:07:27,879 --> 00:07:30,439
Mr. Sheng, what took you so long?

152
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,120
What, did I come at a bad time?

153
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:35,279
Of course not.

154
00:07:35,439 --> 00:07:36,759
You came at exactly the right time.

155
00:07:36,959 --> 00:07:37,600
Please.

156
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,480
Hold on.

157
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:41,160
First, let me introduce a new friend.

158
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:46,000
A renowned oncologist from Germany.

159
00:07:46,399 --> 00:07:47,199
Dr. Yiwen Zhang.

160
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:15,720
First, treat Dr. Yiwen Zhang's assistant

161
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,839
as Dr. Yiwen Zhang and bring him in,

162
00:08:17,959 --> 00:08:19,399
so the watchers take the bait.

163
00:08:19,959 --> 00:08:21,600
Then I'll call the real Dr. Yiwen Zhang

164
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,920
and get him to Benevolence Hospital.

165
00:08:35,279 --> 00:08:37,559
I'm sure you've all heard of

166
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:38,720
Dr. Yiwen Zhang.

167
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:41,840
I invited Dr. Yiwen Zhang here today

168
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,639
to recommend him as

169
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,519
Benevolence Hospital's new president.

170
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,840
And under his leadership,

171
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:53,440
we'll build the world's top Cancer Center.

172
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,120
Miss Lin.

173
00:08:55,679 --> 00:08:57,279
Aren't you being a little full of yourself?

174
00:08:57,639 --> 00:08:59,559
Shareholders care about returns.

175
00:08:59,879 --> 00:09:02,519
No matter how great this Cancer Center is,

176
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:05,480
it won't beat the VIP Center for profit.

177
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:07,759
But a hospital's core strength is its doctors.

178
00:09:08,639 --> 00:09:09,759
Aren't you even going to hear

179
00:09:09,759 --> 00:09:11,120
what the doctors think?

180
00:09:12,799 --> 00:09:13,519
What's so special about that?

181
00:09:13,519 --> 00:09:14,080
That's right.

182
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:15,159
He's right.

183
00:09:15,159 --> 00:09:16,519
That's right.

184
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,039
Yeah.

185
00:09:17,559 --> 00:09:18,399
Looking for trouble?

186
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:24,159
Then let's take a democratic vote.

187
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,000
Those in favor of Dr. Yiwen Zhang

188
00:09:26,519 --> 00:09:28,360
as Benevolence Healthcare's new president,

189
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:30,320
and establishing a Cancer Center,

190
00:09:30,519 --> 00:09:31,200
please raise your hand.

191
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,759
Thank you all for your support.

192
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,200
Then I announce

193
00:10:02,639 --> 00:10:03,639
Dr. Yiwen Zhang

194
00:10:03,639 --> 00:10:06,360
is officially Benevolence Hospital's new president.

195
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:25,799
Chairman Sheng, it was going smoothly.

196
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,600
It was all because of your son, Sheng Yuanzhou.

197
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:28,120
He suddenly...

198
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:30,200
Enough. I know.

199
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:32,320
You have to stand up for me.

200
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:35,399
The shareholders already voted it through.

201
00:10:35,639 --> 00:10:36,559
What can I do?

202
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:41,759
Chairman Sheng, don't kick away the ladder.

203
00:10:47,919 --> 00:10:49,080
Are you threatening me?

204
00:10:51,799 --> 00:10:52,679
Of course not.

205
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,559
You were involved in this too.

206
00:10:54,559 --> 00:10:55,840
Even if you talk,

207
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,440
at best, you'd be turning yourself in.

208
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,320
I promise you,

209
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:00,039
you'll be locked up for life.

210
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,080
Chairman Sheng...

211
00:11:03,759 --> 00:11:05,840
I'm definitely on your side.

212
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,799
I won't say a single word.

213
00:11:08,159 --> 00:11:09,759
It's best that you understand that.

214
00:11:10,159 --> 00:11:12,600
Put the hospital matter aside for now.

215
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,279
We'll figure something out later.

216
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:16,919
Okay.

217
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,639
I'll do as you say.

218
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,399
Siqi.

219
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:23,720
What are you thinking about?

220
00:11:26,159 --> 00:11:26,759
Nothing.

221
00:11:27,159 --> 00:11:27,879
Xiaobei.

222
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,360
Thank you for everything lately.

223
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,879
For standing by me through the hard times.

224
00:11:32,759 --> 00:11:34,279
Wasn't that what I was supposed to do?

225
00:11:35,159 --> 00:11:37,519
Honestly, I didn't do much.

226
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:39,639
Sheng Yuanzhou did most of it.

227
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:44,279
He did do a lot.

228
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:48,000
He seems to have changed a lot too.

229
00:11:49,159 --> 00:11:51,559
It's like he's become a different person.

230
00:11:58,480 --> 00:11:59,559
Actually...

231
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:02,360
So have you.

232
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:05,360
Not exactly.

233
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,399
But also...

234
00:12:09,559 --> 00:12:10,559
Anyway, Xiaobei, it's just...

235
00:12:10,559 --> 00:12:13,000
I feel like we've both changed a lot lately.

236
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,120
But I can't really put it into words.

237
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:14,720
I get what you mean.

238
00:12:20,159 --> 00:12:23,120
I actually feel the same way.

239
00:12:23,399 --> 00:12:26,240
I should've been the one who knew you best,

240
00:12:27,159 --> 00:12:28,480
the one who could help you most.

241
00:12:29,679 --> 00:12:31,480
But everything from before feels

242
00:12:32,279 --> 00:12:33,480
so unfamiliar to me.

243
00:12:37,799 --> 00:12:40,120
Even though I'm happy with you,

244
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:42,279
but...

245
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:44,759
But I respect your choice.

246
00:12:58,519 --> 00:12:59,320
But...

247
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,519
You used to

248
00:13:03,919 --> 00:13:07,159
never give up on me so easily.

249
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:08,679
I...

250
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:11,120
I just want you to be happy.

251
00:13:11,519 --> 00:13:12,639
I don't even know what I should say...

252
00:13:12,639 --> 00:13:13,240
I understand.

253
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:14,399
Xiaobei.

254
00:13:17,799 --> 00:13:18,559
Thank you.

255
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:22,840
I'll head home first.

256
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,799
Take good care of yourself from now on.

257
00:13:28,679 --> 00:13:29,320
I...

258
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:32,840
I'll head home.

259
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,399
Siqi's engagement is called off.

260
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:02,600
The family issues are mostly resolved too.

261
00:14:02,799 --> 00:14:04,679
In five days, I'll be Zhang Xiaobei again.

262
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:05,759
That's great.

263
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:29,320
Come on, Xiaobei.

264
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:30,879
Give it a taste. How is it?

265
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:37,360
Come on, give it a taste. How is it?

266
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:38,360
Sir.

267
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:39,440
Sir.

268
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,159
Sir.

269
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:41,799
What do you think?

270
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:43,919
These are all move-in-ready units.

271
00:14:44,159 --> 00:14:45,480
You just need to bring your bags.

272
00:14:45,919 --> 00:14:47,120
There are two supermarkets downstairs.

273
00:14:47,279 --> 00:14:48,360
And once you step out, the subway station

274
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:49,200
is just over 100 meters away.

275
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:50,000
And it's a transfer station.

276
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:50,879
Super convenient.

277
00:14:51,279 --> 00:14:52,639
No traffic jams during your commute.

278
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:54,000
I'll take this one.

279
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:55,720
Buying a house?

280
00:14:56,159 --> 00:14:56,600
Yes.

281
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:57,879
And on the property registration,

282
00:14:57,879 --> 00:14:59,000
it's under Zhang Xiaobei's name.

283
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:01,679
Zhang Xiaobei.

284
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,159
Have Yuanzhou come see me.

285
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:07,919
Yes, sir.

286
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:13,799
Zhang Xiaobei...

287
00:15:16,039 --> 00:15:17,200
He's already decided to mortgage

288
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,559
that plot in Baizimei.

289
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:22,759
Young Mr. Sheng asked about the heir issue.

290
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:26,759
He showed no signs of any panic disorder at all.

291
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:34,720
Father.

292
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:45,919
Father.

293
00:15:46,159 --> 00:15:47,279
About the Benevolence Hospital matter,

294
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,559
I was looking at it from the perspective

295
00:15:49,559 --> 00:15:50,360
of the company's interests.

296
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:53,080
Jiang Min's premium healthcare building...

297
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,120
forty percent of its construction funds

298
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:56,679
would go straight into his own pocket.

299
00:15:56,919 --> 00:15:59,559
After all, our group is investing in it.

300
00:15:59,759 --> 00:16:01,879
We can't let such a parasite take over.

301
00:16:05,279 --> 00:16:06,279
You don't need to explain.

302
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,759
The Benevolence Hospital matter,

303
00:16:09,879 --> 00:16:11,600
I didn't care much about it anyway.

304
00:16:11,759 --> 00:16:13,960
If you want to play savior, that's up to you.

305
00:16:14,159 --> 00:16:15,320
All I care about is

306
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:18,240
whether you're fit to be my heir.

307
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:24,039
You're in charge of this project now.

308
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:31,200
You want to tear down Commoners' Alley?

309
00:16:31,639 --> 00:16:32,600
Isn't that my home?
